text: Miral Abdelkader (born 16 November 1983) is an Egyptian volleyball player. She was a member of Egypt women's national volleyball team. She participated in the 2002 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship and 2006 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship in Japan. On the club level, she played with Al Ahly Women's Volleyball. == References == Category:1983 births Category:Living people Category:Egyptian sportspeople Category:Volleyball players
